&lt;p&gt;The Department of EEE in association with Women Empowerment Cell of &amp;nbsp;Sree Vidyanikethan Engineering College launched IEEE Women In Engineering (WIE) Affinity Group on 13&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; September 2019.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr.P.C.Krishnamachary Principal, SVEC; Dr.L.Venugopal Reddy, Advisor Cum Director, SVET; Guest of Honour, Dr.Neelima Sathyam, Associate Professor IIT Indore; Chief Guest&amp;nbsp; Dr.K.Madhavi,&amp;nbsp; IEEE WIE Chair, Anantapur subsection JNTUA CEA Anantapur, Directors, Deans and HoDs graced the occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the welcome address, Dr. M. Sujatha Professor &amp;amp; Head, Department of EEE told that the objective of the initiation was to promote&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; IEEE &amp;amp; IEEE WIE by recruiting more members and volunteers to participate in IEEE WIE. During the address, Ms. Sujatha highlighted that IEEE WIE is one of the largest international professional organizations dedicated to promote women engineers &amp;amp; scientists and inspire girls around the world to follow their academic interests to a career in Engineering. Also, she read out the statistical data of colleges involved in IEEE WIE in various colleges and advised students to take memberships and be a part of IEEE WIE.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Women in engineering special session on Obstacles or opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;yiv0920665452MsoNormal&quot;&gt;This positive vibe was spread by Dr. Sandhya Kode Director, Training and Development, IIIT Hyderabad. She began the session by explaining how to turn obstacles into&amp;nbsp;opportunities. Ability to learn and life long journey, collaboration, communication skills, integrity leveraging the technology and leveraging strength were some of the points shared by her. She insisted on some important points such as the right way to treat other people is how you want to be treated and choosing the right thing in difficult situations is the real life. She concluded her speech by motivating the gathering to strengthen the core, exercise, build resilience especially adversity quotient to turn obstacles into opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;yiv0920665452MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The woman in Engineering Affinity Group (WIE AG), IEEE-Hyderabad Section, is organizing this Professional Development Program. We invite Industry Professionals, Young Professionals / Faculty in Academic Institutions and Research Scholars/ Students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The woman in Engineering Affinity Group (WIE AG), IEEE Hyderabad Section has initiated a New Lecture Series in the memory of &quot;Ayyalasomayajula Lalitha&quot;, the First Woman Engineer in India. This is a second flagship event of WIE AG, the IEEE Hyderabad Section. The vision of initiation of this lecture is&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&quot;&lt;/strong&gt;minimizing the gender gap and assist the sustainable development of our country for Science, Technology, Innovation, and Entrepreneurship among woman&quot;. The mission of this lecture is&amp;nbsp;to promote, to excel, to motivate young girls towards STEM, to make every woman to participate and reach their goals professionally,&amp;nbsp;to emphasize, to retain and bring back the women dropping out in large numbers in mid-career into workforce and&amp;nbsp;to inculcate a &amp;ldquo;career identity&amp;rdquo; in strong young brains, which makes them to handle the demands of their personal and professional lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More details about IEEE-Hyderabad Section &amp;nbsp;are at&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ieeehyd.org/&quot;&gt;www.ieeehyd.org&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abstract of the Second LML:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Challenges of a Woman Technopreneur in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Electronics Manufacturing Sector&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abstract:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The journey of an entrepreneur is inherently tedious and prone to obstacles. Being a woman, working with the electronics hardware sector, and putting the entire setup in the 1960s adds many extra layers of complexity. Ms. Durga Rao&#39;s story is exactly how it all unfolds, and the success of her firm, Sulakshana Circuits Limited, is an epitome of her perseverance and self-confidence. Inspiration comes from reading such stories, but some real people are so down to earth and approachable that listening to their story from them is a possible, life-changing experience that urges us to do more within our limitations in our own lives. This talk is thus the life lesson that a lot of us must immerse in and learn.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brief details of the Major Topics that will be covered in the above Lecture are as follows:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This LML is aimed to attain the below objectives&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To encourage more young women to enter the STEM fields for the profession and to continue their careers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To encourage the participation of women in our country in all aspects of the scientific fields including education, teaching, research, leadership, employment, and decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To promote the recognition of the scientific and technological achievements of women scientist and technologist in our country,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To increase the access of women to the socio-economic benefits of science and technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To promote collaboration and communication among women scientists and technologists with the international scientific community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To increase understanding of the role of science and technology in supporting Women&amp;rsquo;s development activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IEEE AHCSSC 2020 is third of its kind, a flagship event conference from the Hyderabad Section of the IEEE Computer Society.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The theme of this congress is&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&quot;Digital Reality, Artificial Intelligence, Robotics&quot;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;and it aims to bring members from different student branches together to collaborate on new ideas and get awareness about the latest trends in computing technologies.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On this congress a special session for Women in Engineering members is organized by Chief guest and speaker Mrs. Rama Devi Lanka, OSD-Telangana, IT Department on &quot;Emerging technologies in Digital&quot; which is taking place on 3rd January, 2020.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For a developing country &amp;nbsp;many problems to be solved and&amp;nbsp; these problems need technology based solutions. This seminar gave students the boost to start working on our career and solve the technology solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
